   "source": [
    "This step combines the metadata (`tmdb_movies`) and cast/crew information (`tmdb_credits`) into a single dataset (`tmdb_full`) based on `title`. By dropping unnecessary columns, we streamline the dataset, making it easier to work with making sure only relevant information is retained. This prepares the data for further preprocessing and merging."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "47460cf8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# merging our two tmdb datasets\n",
    "tmdb_movies['title'] = tmdb_movies['title'].astype(str)\n",
    "tmdb_credits['title'] = tmdb_credits['title'].astype(str)\n",
    "\n",
    "tmdb_full = pd.merge(tmdb_movies, tmdb_credits, on='title', how='inner')\n",
    "\n",
    "# dropping unnecessary columns\n",
    "tmdb_full = tmdb_full.drop(columns=['id', 'tagline', 'status','overview', 'keywords', 'homepage', 'original_title', 'popularity', 'production_companies', 'production_countries', 'revenue', 'cast', 'spoken_languages'])\n",
    "tmdb_full.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9c45a4ca",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Our next objective is to adjust the budget values in our `tmdb_full` dataset to account for inflation. We follow the same process we did for the revenues previously. We alos drop the `cpi` and the original `budget` columns because they are irrelevant now. After adjusting the budget, we rearrange the columns to make it more organized."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "1c2a1c19",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# adjust for budget with cpi (same process as before)\n",
    "tmdb_full['release_date'] = pd.to_datetime(tmdb_full['release_date'])\n",
    "tmdb_full['year'] = tmdb_full['release_date'].dt.year\n",
    "\n",
    "tmdb_full = tmdb_full.merge(yearly_cpi, on='year', how='left')\n",
    "tmdb_full['budget'] = pd.to_numeric(tmdb_full['budget'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "\n",
    "tmdb_full['budget_adjusted'] = tmdb_full['budget'] * (latest_cpi / tmdb_full['cpi'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# dropping cpi\n",
    "tmdb_full = tmdb_full.drop(columns=['cpi', 'budget'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# rearranging rows\n",
    "tmdb_full = tmdb_full[['movie_id', 'title', 'genres','original_language', 'year', 'release_date', 'budget_adjusted','crew', 'vote_average', \"vote_count\"]]\n",
    "tmdb_full"
   ]
  },
